parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty positive battery terminal cable can cause the engine control module (ECM) to fail, leading to the vehicle stalling or not starting, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or fails to start
battery drain
electrical system malfunctions
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while in motion can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls while driving
loss of power
and difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause loss of acceleration, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
transmission slipping or failure to engage gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake system failure can cause loss of braking ability, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle's brakes lock up or fail to engage
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag and electrical system malfunctions can cause the airbag to fail to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
electrical system malfunctions
and failure of other safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the deployment of airbags without a crash, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on or flashes
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the passenger airbag light stays on or off even when a passenger is present
the airbag is extremely hot when it deploys.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the deployment of airbags without a crash, or the failure to deploy airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on or flashes
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the passenger airbag light stays on or off even when a passenger is present.

symptoms: The airbag light comes on or flashes
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power without warning
often accompanied by a check engine light
and may require restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, and oil leaks can cause damage to other components and create a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
often with no visible external leaks
and may require frequent oil top-offs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty engine valves and lifters can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences valve knocking or lifter noise
often accompanied by a check engine light
and may require engine repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cooling system leaks and failures can cause engine overheating, damage, and stalling, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences coolant leaks
overheating
or engine damage
often accompanied by a check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ECM failures can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and other electrical system malfunctions, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences engine stalling
loss of power
or other electrical system malfunctions
often accompanied by a check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission issues can cause loss of power, stalling, and difficulty shifting gears, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences clutch or transmission problems
often accompanied by a check engine light
and may require repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or become stuck in a particular gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls

or becomes stuck in a particular gear; the transmission goes into "safe mode" and limits the vehicle's speed; the vehicle jerks or makes a noise when shifting gears; the transmission fails to engage or disengage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut-off of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine shuts off or stalls without warning; the vehicle loses power; the engine restarts after a short period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission gear control can cause the vehicle to become stuck in a particular gear, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission gear control becomes stuck or locked; the vehicle is unable to shift into other gears; the transmission makes a noise or jerks when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause various problems, including engine stalling, transmission failure, and loss of motive power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions; the engine stalls or shuts off; the transmission fails to engage or disengage properly; the vehicle's lights or dashboard instruments malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the knock sensor or oxygen sensor can cause the engine to adjust timing incorrectly, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The engine bucks or misfires; the catalytic converter overheats or fails; the vehicle's engine performance is poor.
